 is more probably a variant of   Alger   (Old Norse <i>Álfgeirr</i>). See also   Agar  ,   Elgar  ."]},{"name":"Alker","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Frieda, Gerhart.","South German: variant of   Alger  .","English: habitational name from Altcar, Lancashire. This name means ‘marshland by the River Alt’, from Old Norse <i>kjarr</i> ‘marsh’ and the river name <i>Alt</i>."]},{"name":"Ager","meanings":["English (mainly Essex, Suffolk, and Northamptonshire): variant of   Alger   or possibly of   Edgar  .","Danish: habitational name from any of several places called Ager, meaning ‘plowed land’ (from a cognate of the English word <i>acre</i>).","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Adgari</i>, composed of the elements <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>gari</i> (from <i>garwa</i>) ‘ready, eager’ or <i>gari</i> ‘spear’. This surname is very rare in France."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Alger was born about 1315, in Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with John Alger."},"et":{"about 1315–":"umbes 1315–Surnud","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1333–1412":"1333–1412","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1315":"1315","1412":"1412","1313":"1313","1333":"1333","about 1315":"umbes 1315","Lindsell, Essex, England":"Lindsell, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Lindsell, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1315–":"noin 1315–Kuollut","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1333–1412":"1333–1412","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1412":"1412","1313":"1313","1333":"1333","about 1315":"noin 1315","Lindsell, Essex, England":"Lindsell, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Lindsell, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1315–":"environ 1315–Décédée","1313–Male":"1313–Décédé","1333–1412":"1333–1412","